docs.lead_paragraph: UNITED NATIONS, N. Y., Sept. 30 -- President Arthur da Costa e Silva of Brazil, where the economy is growing at a strong 6 per cent this year, lamented recently to a diplomatic visitor that the benefits of this growth are being diluted by a soaring population.

headline.main: Birth Rates Strain Developing Economies; POPULATION GAINS STRAIN ECONOMIES

docs.abstract: article on effect of population growth on econ of various nations in light of McNamara s; graphs of population growth and per-capita income
